Conder Group PLC said it received clearance to proceed with its merger with Beaman Corp. 

In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Conder said the Federal Trade Commission notified it on Sept. 6 that its request for early termination of a required waiting period had been granted. 

As previously reported, Beaman agreed to be acquired by Conder, of Winchester, England, for $7 a share.
Beaman is based in Greensboro, N.C. 

